H0.text: The name of which European capital city means Merchants Harbour. Stockholm

H1.text: The name of which European capital city means Merchants Harbour. Helsinki

H2.text: The name of which European capital city means Merchants Harbour. Riga

H3.text: The name of which European capital city means Merchants Harbour. DKCPH

A4.text: The original designation in Old Norse, from which Danish descends, was Kaupmannahǫfn [ˈkɔupˌmɑnːɑˌhɔvn] (cf. modern Icelandic: Kaupmannahöfn [ˈkʰœipˌmanːaˌhœpn̥], Faroese: Keypmannahavn [ˈtʃʰɛʰpmanːaˌhavn]), meaning 'merchants' harbour' (merchant in plural).

A5.text: By the time Old Danish was spoken, the capital was called Køpmannæhafn, with the current name deriving from centuries of subsequent regular sound change.
